comments: White (BOS) is moving alongside Irving's (BKN) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during the drive.
White (BOS) brushes Irving's (BKN) right shoulder after the release of his jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs.
Horford (BOS) engages and disengages with Claxton (BKN) after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Durant (BKN) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another as Tatum moves along the perimeter to set the pick.
Irving (BKN) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another as the defensive switch occurs during the pick.
Brown (BOS) and Brown (BKN) come together at the same spot in the lane and marginal contact occurs before they disengage with one another during rebounding.

Curry (BKN) fully extends both hands against Brown's (BOS) back and delivers contact that alters Brown's body trajectory as he elevates for the rebound. This contact causes the subsequent contact between Claxton (BKN) and Brown thereafter.
White (BOS) brings his hands toward Durant's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs with Durant's front as he dribbles toward the wing.
White (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball and the part of Durant's (BKN) hand that is on the ball, causing it to become loose at the end of Durant's drive.
Brown (BOS) and Durant (BKN) come together at the same spot in the lane and incidental body contact occurs as Durant is already losing control of the ball.
Brown (BOS) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Durant's (BKN) slightly extended right leg during the follow-through.
Durant (BKN) brings his hands toward Tatum's (BOS) back and marginal contact occurs as Tatum slips the pick at the top of the perimeter.
Irving (BKN) is turning alongside Smart's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs as Smart drives inside the perimeter.

Curry (BKN) establishes himself in Smart's (BOS) path and marginal leg-to-leg contact occurs as Smart attempts to slip by toward the basket. Irving (BKN) maintains a rested hand on Smart's left hip and releases away without applying any force as he absorbs the marginal contact thereafter.
Curry (BKN) brushes Horford's (BOS) right arm and Horford is able to move through the marginal contact to finish at the rim.
Tatum (BOS) initiates contact with Durant (BKN) off ball that re-routes him and affects his FOM.
Smart (BOS) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Irving's (BKN) right shoulder after the release.
Durant (BKN) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another as the screen approaches.
Brown (BKN) brings his left arm toward Brown's (BOS) left side and marginal contact occurs after Brown's (BOS) gather.
As Brown (BOS) slows down during his drive to the basket, he removes his off-arm from Brown's (BKN) midsection and Brown's momentum carries him away from the play.
Smart (BOS) brings his hand toward Irving's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs with Irving's front prior to incidental foot-to-foot contact being made.
Horford (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Smart's (BOS) left arm is extended in Irving's (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs with Irving's front as he changes direction during the drive.

Horford (BOS) is moving forward slightly toward Irving (BKN) and marginal body contact occurs after Irving picks up his dribble in the post. Simultaneously, Smart (BOS) comes to double Irving and marginal contact occurs with Irving's left side as he is passing.
Irving (BKN) maintains his left foot as his pivot after picking up his dribble.
Durant (BKN) and Tatum (BOS) come together at the same spot along the perimeter and marginal contact occurs as Durant releases his off-arm away from Tatum's front.
Tatum (BOS) legally contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Claxton (BKN) brushes Horford's (BOS) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Horford secures the rebound.
Dragic (BKN) turns alongside Brown's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.
Dragic (BKN) brings a rested hand and bent forearm toward Brown's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs as Brown dribbles in the post.
Tatum (BOS) gathers the pass on his right foot and takes one step on his left foot before he elevates for the layup.

Irving (BKN) brushes Tatum's (BOS) left side/right arm as Tatum gathers and enters his upward shooting motion, and the contact is marginal. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that Tatum releases the shot attempt prior to the expiration of the game clock.
